╭─ Assistant [MainThread@3853950] ─────────────────────────────╮
│ An analysis of the bug reveals that the SLP vectorizer's     │
│ horizontal reduction logic incorrectly attempts to delete    │
│ scalar instructions that are part of a recurrence. This      │
│ premature deletion of live instructions leads to an          │
│ assertion failure.                                           │
│                                                              │
│ The issue occurs in `BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree` when it's       │
│ called for horizontal reduction. In this context, the        │
│ function is not supposed to delete the original scalar       │
│ instructions, as they might still be live due to             │
│ loop-carried dependencies. The responsibility for cleaning   │
│ up the now-redundant scalar code should be left to           │
│ subsequent dead code elimination passes, which can safely    │
│ handle recurrences.                                          │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to prevent `BoUpSLP::vectorizeTree` from deleting │
│ the scalar instructions when it's invoked for a horizontal   │
│ reduction. We can identify this specific invocation by       │
│ checking the `ReductionRoot` parameter. If `ReductionRoot`   │
│ is not null, it signifies a horizontal reduction, and we     │
│ should skip the instruction removal step.                    │
│                                                              │
│ The following patch implements this logic by guarding the    │
│ call to `removeInstructionsAndOperands` with a check on      │
│ `ReductionRoot`.                                             │
│                                                              │
│ ```patch                                                     │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp        │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp        │
│ @@ -15716,7 +15716,7 @@                                      │
│    // cache correctness.                                     │
│    // NOTE: removeInstructionAndOperands only marks the      │
│ instruction for deletion                                     │
│    // - instructions are not deleted until later.            │
│ -  removeInstructionsAndOperands(ArrayRef(RemovedInsts));    │
│ +  if (!ReductionRoot)                                       │
│ +    removeInstructionsAndOperands(ArrayRef(RemovedInsts));  │
│                                                              │
│    Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();                            │
│    InstrElementSize.clear();                                 │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
